<title type="html"><![CDATA[Eating in Restaurants which have in them Alcohol – Shaykh Al-Albani]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=544&amp;p=586#p586"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="color: #FF0000">The Questioner: On the ruling on eating in restaurants which have in them alcohol, some brothers raise the issue that there is other than the it (alcohol) present?</span></strong><br /><br /><span style="color: #0040FF"><strong>Shaikh Al Albani rahimahullah: that there is other than alcohol?</strong></span><br /><br />Questioner: Yes<br /><br />Shaikh: We do not doubt in the impermissibility because it is entering into places in which Allah’s punishment and anger are permissible. So it is not permissible for a Muslim except for one passing through.<br /><br />Questioner: He buys to-go?<br /><br />Shaikh: As long as there is other than it (alcohol) in it, there is no hindrance for the one on the go.<br /><br />[Taken from Silsilatul Huda wan-Noor no. 62]<br /><br />Translated by<br /><br />Faisal ibn Abdul Qaadir ibn Hassan<br /><br />Abu Sulaymaan<br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://darussaafi.wordpress.com/2014/03/05/eating-in-restaurants-which-have-in-them-alcohol-shaykh-al-albani/">https://darussaafi.wordpress.com/2014/0 ... al-albani/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Fri Oct 28, 2016 11:34 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
